    ],
    "text": "Former IGP Dies from Gunshot Injury The Malabe Police Station has launched an investigation following information received on the morning of 17 July 2026 that former Inspector General of Police (IGP) C.D. Wickramaratne had died after being admitted to the Colombo East Teaching Hospital with a gunshot injury sustained at his residence on Parakrama Road, Talahena, within the Malabe Police Division. The body has been placed at the Colombo East Teaching Hospital for a post-mortem examination. Further investigations are being carried out by the Western Province Southern District Crime Division in collaboration with the Malabe Police Station. C.D. Wickramaratne served as the 35th Inspector General of Police of Sri Lanka from 27 November 2020 to 23 November 2023. He was 63 years old at the time of his death. Police Media Division",
